        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 24:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 28:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) The Septuagint phrase is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "θαυμάσαι πρόσωπον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which St. Jude adopts (ver. 16). Other writers in the New Testament use ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "λαμβάνειν πρόσωτον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in the same sense; ",
